    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "5be189a78ece4a67",
      "text": "What makes a commons is **stewarding**; unstewarded, a ‘commons’ is simply an unregulated common pool - the kind of thing parodied in Garrett Hardin’s  ill-conceived, rational-actor parody of commons as ‘a tragedy’. Thus stewarding of commons is a particularly important family of patterns to be curated and mobilised in the college. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "6ae53804f8642e83",
      "text": "This is not simple, since, as underlined for example by the investigations of David Bollier and Silke Helfrich \\[Bollier & Helfrich xxx], each commons is particular: its own means to curate and contribute, its own patterns of enjoying and mobilising; and its own necessities and traditions of stewarding.\n\n"
    },
